A weathered stone cemetery tombstone standing alone in an overgrown field at dusk, with wild vines and dead flowers creeping up its base. The tombstone casts a long shadow across scattered envelopes and paper letters decomposing into the earth around it. A single crow perches atop the monument. The sky is overcast with dramatic purple and orange sunset colors breaking through storm clouds. The scene has a melancholic, contemplative atmosphere with rich photorealistic detail—moss textures on stone, individual blades of grass, water droplets on wilting petals. No text or writing visible anywhere on the tombstone or papers.
